  "title": "Electrical & Instrumentation Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Support the maintenance, calibration, and troubleshooting of electrical and instrumentation systems in a pharmaceutical manufacturing environment, ensuring safe, compliant, and reliable operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain and troubleshoot electrical and instrumentation equipment in production areas to ensure continuous, compliant manufacturing operations</li><li>Assist in the installation, calibration, testing, and commissioning of electrical and instrumentation systems to meet regulatory and operational standards</li><li>Prepare and maintain accurate technical documentation and equipment records to support GMP compliance and audit readiness</li><li>Ensure adherence to GMP, safety, and regulatory standards through proactive system support and compliance monitoring</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive process improvements and support project execution within the manufacturing environment</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Electrical or Instrumentation Engineering</li><li>1–3 years of experience in electrical/instrumentation engineering, preferably in pharmaceutical or regulated manufacturing environments</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of control systems, instrumentation, and calibration techniques</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills demonstrated through effective troubleshooting in regulated manufacturing settings</li><li>Proven teamwork abilities contributing to cross-functional collaboration and process improvements</li><li>Attention to detail in maintaining compliance documentation and operational standards</li></ul>",
